01:25.686 --> 01:29.213
Joanie, we're going
to Parent-Teacher Day

01:29.323 --> 01:30.551
and talk to your teachers.

01:30.657 --> 01:33.320
Fine, but you don't have
to believe everything they say.

01:33.427 --> 01:35.361
You're not trying to hide
something from us,

01:35.462 --> 01:36.827
are you, sweetheart?

01:36.930 --> 01:39.456
No. I'm doing the same fantastic
work I've always done.

01:39.566 --> 01:42.797
I don't care what
my geometry teacher says.

01:42.903 --> 01:45.838
Well, we'll try
and keep that in mind.

01:45.939 --> 01:47.031
Bye-bye, Richard.

01:47.140 --> 01:48.164
Good luck, son.

01:48.275 --> 01:49.970
Oh, thanks, Dad.

01:50.077 --> 01:52.511
I'll be the one
who needs the luck.

01:55.015 --> 01:57.711
(chuckles)
Oh, that Lori Beth's cute.

01:57.818 --> 02:00.878
Not cute when she ties
my shoes together like this.

02:02.022 --> 02:04.115
- Hey, Richie.
- Oh, hi, Fonz.

02:04.224 --> 02:05.589
How ya doing?

02:07.227 --> 02:09.217
Listen...

02:09.329 --> 02:11.559
I just, I'm returning your
parents' albums right here.

02:11.665 --> 02:12.860
They lent them to me, all right?

02:12.966 --> 02:13.990
- Yeah. Fonz...
- You tell 'em.

02:14.101 --> 02:15.068
...you gonna come down

02:15.168 --> 02:16.568
and see the kid tear 'em up
tonight?

02:16.670 --> 02:18.536
Oh! Intramural action
at its finest.

02:18.639 --> 02:19.663
<i>Hm!</i>

02:19.773 --> 02:20.831
No.

02:20.941 --> 02:21.965
Oh.

02:22.075 --> 02:23.839
I'm going down
to the ballet studio.

02:23.944 --> 02:25.070
Oh, to pick up Colleen?

02:25.178 --> 02:27.044
Okay, I got an idea, Lori Beth's
down there, too.

02:27.147 --> 02:29.172
Pick 'em both up,
bring them all to the game.

02:29.282 --> 02:30.614
Oh, it's gonna be
a terrific one, Fonz--

02:30.717 --> 02:31.616
playing for first place.

02:31.718 --> 02:33.618
No.

02:33.720 --> 02:36.849
See, Richard,
Colleen and I got other plans.

02:36.957 --> 02:38.356
Oh.

02:38.458 --> 02:40.085
-(car horn honks)
- I better get going.

02:40.193 --> 02:41.593
You know, I'll tell you
something.

02:41.695 --> 02:45.359
I can't tell you how classy this
chick is, my little ballerina--

02:45.465 --> 02:47.365
she has made
a new man out of me.

02:47.467 --> 02:48.491
Yeah, that's great, Fonz.

02:48.602 --> 02:49.831
Potsie and Ralph
are out there, and I have...

02:49.936 --> 02:51.427
- You know something?
Look at this. -Huh?

02:51.538 --> 02:55.566
She's got me listening
to classical music, huh?

02:55.676 --> 02:58.975
- Mantovani...
- Mantovani?

02:59.079 --> 03:00.513
Yeah, Mantovani is nice.

03:00.614 --> 03:02.138
Yeah, Al's out there, too. I...

03:02.249 --> 03:05.912
Do you know that she is unlike
any other chick I know?

03:06.019 --> 03:08.750
That when I snap my fingers,
she don't just come to me.

03:08.855 --> 03:11.654
This butterfly, she glides.

03:11.758 --> 03:13.385
Uh, Fonz, I-l really got to go.

03:13.493 --> 03:15.291
I mean, we're providing
the game ball and...

03:15.395 --> 03:16.522
You know what happened
last night?

03:16.630 --> 03:18.564
This is really gonna
put a snap in your trunks.

03:18.665 --> 03:19.655
All right,
all right, tell me.

03:21.768 --> 03:25.261
She ate her soup
without making any noise.

03:28.408 --> 03:29.307
Oh, my gosh!

03:29.409 --> 03:30.775
I told you.

03:30.877 --> 03:33.005
Oh, I'm gonna have to tell
the guys about that! See ya!

03:33.113 --> 03:34.103
Oh, all right.

03:37.718 --> 03:40.448
Turn. That's not it.

03:40.554 --> 03:42.351
No, no, no, try it this way.

03:47.227 --> 03:49.093
Colleen, you're so good.

03:49.196 --> 03:51.687
Why are you wasting
your time here?

03:51.798 --> 03:53.994
Why don't you go to New York
and become a professional?

03:54.101 --> 03:56.069
Oh, I just couldn't find
a suitcase big enough

03:56.169 --> 03:57.728
to pack all my mirrors.

03:57.838 --> 04:01.501
I know, you don't want
to talk about it.

04:01.608 --> 04:03.372
Listen, I better call it a day.

04:03.477 --> 04:05.775
I'm late for Richie's
basketball game.

04:05.879 --> 04:09.713
Want to come along
or are you waiting for Fonzie?

04:09.816 --> 04:11.512
Yeah.

04:11.618 --> 04:14.053
You're really stuck on him, huh?

04:14.154 --> 04:15.314
He's so thoughtful.

04:15.422 --> 04:17.914
Last night,
all I did was mention

04:18.024 --> 04:19.959
that I liked fresh flowers,

04:20.060 --> 04:24.019
and he stopped the bike and
dug up two wild azalea bushes.

04:24.131 --> 04:27.225
Sounds like true love to me.

04:27.334 --> 04:28.699
Listen, I better get going.

04:28.802 --> 04:31.328
Last time I was late for
Richie's basketball game,

04:31.438 --> 04:33.304
he fined me two dollars.

04:33.406 --> 04:35.534
Chassé, pas de bourrée,

04:35.642 --> 04:36.632
and pirou...

04:36.743 --> 04:38.711
I'll work on it.

04:38.812 --> 04:41.178
Good luck with Fonzie.

04:45.452 --> 04:48.581
<i>COLLEEN: I had a wonderful time
last night.</i>

04:48.688 --> 04:50.520
<i>I</i> planted the azaleas.

04:55.629 --> 04:56.653
My little ballerina,

04:56.763 --> 04:59.232
I taste a little sadness
on your lips there.

04:59.332 --> 05:01.198
What's-what's going on
in your brain?

05:01.301 --> 05:02.928
Oh, nothing.

05:03.036 --> 05:05.835
Hey, I'm not just a gardener;
you can tell me.

05:07.974 --> 05:11.069
Well, I'm thinking
of closing down the studio.

05:11.178 --> 05:12.702
Why?

05:12.813 --> 05:17.182
Well, you know, five students
aren't exactly profitable.

05:17.284 --> 05:19.878
Maybe I'll go
to New York and study.

05:19.986 --> 05:21.352
New York?
Hey... (chuckles)

05:21.454 --> 05:22.717
you don't have to do that.

05:22.823 --> 05:23.949
You don't got no problem.

05:24.057 --> 05:25.786
You wanted azaleas?
I got you azaleas.

05:25.892 --> 05:27.952
You want students?
I'll get you students.

05:28.061 --> 05:31.554
But Fonzie...
it's not the same as azaleas.

05:31.665 --> 05:32.689
Correct-a-mundo.

05:32.799 --> 05:34.790
Students are easier;
they got no roots.

05:37.337 --> 05:38.532
HOWARD:
Come on, Marion.

05:38.638 --> 05:40.629
We're gonna
to be late for the movie.

05:40.740 --> 05:41.639
Coming, dear.

05:41.741 --> 05:43.573
Is Richard home yet?

05:43.677 --> 05:46.737
Not yet. I guess the game must
have gone into overtime.

05:46.847 --> 05:49.247
You know, I think maybe you
ought to take up basketball.

05:49.349 --> 05:50.942
I got a feeling
that's the only way

05:51.051 --> 05:52.348
you're gonna get to college.

05:52.452 --> 05:55.547
Oh... you know, I don't
understand why you're still mad

05:55.655 --> 05:57.681
about the Parent-Teacher
meeting.

05:57.791 --> 05:58.849
My grades are good.

05:58.959 --> 06:01.587
There are other things
besides grades.

06:01.695 --> 06:04.130
For example,
classroom behavior, huh?

06:04.231 --> 06:06.927
Oh, my behavior isn't that bad.

06:07.033 --> 06:10.401
Is that why the teacher calls
you, "Yak-Yak Face"?

06:12.672 --> 06:13.765
Mr. Stewart's a kidder.

06:13.873 --> 06:16.536
Actually, Yak-Yak Face
is a term of endearment.

06:16.643 --> 06:17.633
Mm...

06:19.045 --> 06:21.446
Yeah, well...

06:24.117 --> 06:26.518
...the kid came through
in the clutch again.

06:26.620 --> 06:28.986
All right, all right, three
seconds left in the game.

06:29.089 --> 06:30.784
Cunningham puts on
the old double fake,

06:30.890 --> 06:33.121
drives in for a hook shot--
swish!

06:33.226 --> 06:35.058
Boom, baby!

06:36.696 --> 06:39.825
Exactly what does
"boom baby" mean, dear?

06:39.933 --> 06:42.595
It means we won the game.

06:42.702 --> 06:44.068
What's going on here?

06:44.170 --> 06:47.140
Oh, right, the, uh,
Parent-Teacher Day.

06:47.240 --> 06:48.935
- Mm.
- How'd it go?

06:49.042 --> 06:50.840
Ask Yak-Yak Face.

06:52.312 --> 06:54.280
You got Mr. Stewart, huh?

06:54.381 --> 06:55.780
Yeah.

06:55.882 --> 06:57.475
See? He's crazy.

06:57.584 --> 07:00.576
Now, if you were in his class,
he'd call you... (laughs)

07:00.687 --> 07:02.485
- Ah...
- Never mind, dear.

07:02.589 --> 07:05.490
Now, we'll be right back as soon
as the movie is over.

07:05.592 --> 07:07.151
And there are sandwiches
in the refrigerator.

07:07.260 --> 07:08.785
JOANIE:
Yeah, Mom.

07:08.895 --> 07:11.558
Hey thanks, Mr. C.
Just the person I want to see.

07:11.665 --> 07:12.757
Close your eyes, visualize,

07:12.866 --> 07:15.198
how'd you like
to take ballet lessons?

07:15.302 --> 07:17.827
Ballet? Oh, I love ballet!

07:17.937 --> 07:21.567
Dancing and jumping,
and being lifted by hunks.

07:21.675 --> 07:23.165
Can I, Dad?

07:23.276 --> 07:27.145
Well, I guess it's all right,
if it doesn't cost me too much.

07:27.247 --> 07:28.578
But you behave yourself.

07:28.682 --> 07:31.276
I don't want to hear the teacher
calling you Yak-Yak Toes.

07:31.384 --> 07:32.442
Thanks, Dad.

07:32.552 --> 07:34.247
Yak-Yak Toes, that's funny,
Yak Yak...

07:34.354 --> 07:35.321
All right, look.

07:35.422 --> 07:36.787
Here, you fill this out Joanie,

07:36.890 --> 07:38.949
-and then you bring this
to class, all right? -Yeah.

07:39.059 --> 07:40.822
You're not gonna regret this,
Mr. C. It's great.

07:40.927 --> 07:43.123
Yeah. Well come on, we're
already late for the movie.

07:43.229 --> 07:46.631
All right, look, Richie...
how about you?

07:50.737 --> 07:51.932
FONZIE:
Okay, <i>I</i> got 'em here.

07:52.038 --> 07:53.130
Now you teach...

07:53.239 --> 07:55.208
you learn.

07:55.308 --> 07:56.639
- Right, Fonz.
- Right.

07:56.743 --> 07:58.336
- All right, class, we can begin.
- Great.

07:58.445 --> 08:00.174
Sorry, I changed my mind.

08:00.280 --> 08:04.308
But no way am I gonna do,
uh, all this stuff.

08:04.417 --> 08:08.047
You dance or you're gonna have
to learn how to walk...

08:08.154 --> 08:10.180
on your hands.

08:10.290 --> 08:13.191
Please, Fonzie,
let's not force anyone.

08:13.293 --> 08:15.557
All right, all right, you're
the boss, you're the boss.

08:15.662 --> 08:16.993
- Play the music.
- All right.

08:17.097 --> 08:18.257
Hey.

08:18.365 --> 08:19.593
Aprés vous--
that's French, you know?

08:19.699 --> 08:21.599
That's good. That's good.

08:21.701 --> 08:23.465
- Everyone over to the barre.
- Come on.

08:23.570 --> 08:27.597
Now, first I'd like to know why
you're all interested in ballet.

08:27.707 --> 08:29.175
I love the ballet.

08:29.275 --> 08:31.141
I ache for the ballet.

08:31.244 --> 08:33.542
Sometimes I even get
ballet aches.

08:33.645 --> 08:34.669
(laughs)

08:40.086 --> 08:43.385
All right, let's start
with grand plié.

08:43.490 --> 08:44.889
I already had dessert.

08:44.991 --> 08:47.051
Lori Beth, you demonstrate.

08:47.160 --> 08:49.219
Chachi, music.

08:49.329 --> 08:52.321
Okay, you start
in first position...

08:52.432 --> 08:53.422
(classical piano music playing)

08:53.533 --> 08:55.695
...and then you sort of squat.

08:55.802 --> 08:57.930
And you keep your back up
straight

08:58.037 --> 08:59.938
and your knees to the side.

09:00.039 --> 09:02.133
My girl. Good.

09:02.242 --> 09:04.267
Now everybody try.

09:04.377 --> 09:07.040
- Oh, this is gonna be
a piece of cake. -Yeah.

09:07.147 --> 09:08.136
(fabric ripping)

09:12.819 --> 09:14.878
Do you have something
I could wear?

09:14.988 --> 09:17.457
All we have are tutus.

09:17.557 --> 09:20.458
A one-one will do.
(laughs)

09:20.560 --> 09:22.892
I've still got it,
even in embarrassment.

09:24.764 --> 09:25.788
All right, everybody turn.

09:25.899 --> 09:27.924
One, two, three,
two, two, three,

09:28.034 --> 09:29.297
three, three, three.

