16:30.823 --> 16:32.120
Of course she's happy.

16:32.225 --> 16:34.216
I mean, uh, look at this,
I got new applications,

16:34.327 --> 16:37.262
her-her classes are thriving,
she's got me, you know.

16:37.363 --> 16:39.092
(laughs)
She's very f...

16:39.198 --> 16:40.529
why do you ask such a thing?

16:40.633 --> 16:42.897
Well, it's just because, uh...

16:43.002 --> 16:46.097
Well, you know she takes
that ballet class in Chicago.

16:46.205 --> 16:48.640
And-and her teacher there
says that he thinks

16:48.741 --> 16:50.505
she might be the best dancer
he's ever seen.

16:50.610 --> 16:52.407
Hey, I know she's
a great dancer.

16:52.511 --> 16:53.979
I ain't bad myself, huh?

16:54.080 --> 16:55.104
Well, yeah, that's true.

16:55.214 --> 16:57.205
But, see, he-he believes
that she might have

16:57.316 --> 16:58.511
the potential to become

16:58.618 --> 17:00.677
a-a great performer.

17:00.786 --> 17:02.812
Hey look, Cunningham,
this is Milwaukee, you know?

17:02.922 --> 17:04.390
You don't get
the cream of the crop here

17:04.490 --> 17:06.788
like the June Taylor Dancers,
you know?

17:06.893 --> 17:08.520
You just leave culture
to me, all right?

17:08.627 --> 17:10.425
Leave the culture to...

17:10.529 --> 17:13.657
Fonzie, she's been training
since she was a little tot!

17:13.766 --> 17:16.428
